President Barack Obama has proclaimed October 7, 2013, as Child Health Day in the United States. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of providing children with a healthy start in life. The Obama Administration has taken steps to prevent bullying, promote a safe school environment, and combat childhood obesity through initiatives like Let's Move! Additionally, the Affordable Care Act has increased access to affordable and quality healthcare for families and children. The President is also taking action to reduce pollution and protect the environment, as clean air and water are vital for a healthy lifestyle. Obama calls on individuals and communities to teach children about nutrition, exercise, and healthy lifestyles by leading by example. He concludes by emphasizing the need to protect and develop the health of children, as they are the future of the nation.